on copies","fa":"The duo's final studio album and their biggest commercial success","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/41/Simon_and_Garfunkel%2C_Bridge_over_Troubled_Water_%281970%29.png"},{"n":"Bat Out of Hell","ar":"Meat Loaf","yr":1977,"sa":"over 43 million copies","fa":"One of the best-selling albums ever, blended rock with theatrical storytelling","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/00/Bat_out_of_Hell.jpg"},{"n":"Jagged Little Pill","ar":"Alanis Morissette","yr":1995,"sa":"over 33 million copies","fa":"Best-selling studio album ever by a female Canadian artist","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/47/Alanis_Morissette_-_Jagged_Little_Pill.jpg"},{"n":"Come Away with Me","ar":"Norah Jones","yr":2002,"sa":"over 27 million copies","fa":"Won Album of the Year at the Grammys, blended jazz, pop and folk","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/00/Norah_Jones_-_Come_Away_With_Me.jpg"},{"n":"Come On Over","ar":"Shania Twain","yr":1997,"sa":"over 40 million copies","fa":"Best-selling studio album by a female artist in country music history","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/0b/ShaniaTwainComeOnOver.png"},{"n":"The Bodyguard: Original Soundtrack Album","ar":"Whitney Houston","yr":1992,"sa":"over 45 million copies","fa":"Best-selling soundtrack album of all time, featuring 'I Will Always Love You'","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/03/Whitney_Houston_-_The_Bodyguard.png"},{"n":"Falling into You","ar":"Celine Dion","yr":1996,"sa":"over 32 million copies","fa":"Won the Grammy for Album of the Year","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/c2/Falling_into_You.png"},{"n":"Let's Talk About Love","ar":"Celine Dion","yr":1997,"sa":"over 31 million copies","fa":"Features 'My Heart Will Go On' from the film Titanic","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/48/Lets_talk_about_love.jpg"},{"n":"A Night at the Opera","ar":"Queen","yr":1975,"sa":"over 6 million copies","fa":"Home to 'Bohemian Rhapsody', one of the most celebrated rock songs ever written","im":null},{"n":"(What's the Story) Morning Glory?","ar":"Oasis","yr":1995,"sa":"over 22 million copies","fa":"One of the best-selling albums in UK chart history","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/b/b1/Oasis_-_%28What%27s_The_Story%29_Morning_Glory_album_cover.jpg"},{"n":"Achtung Baby","ar":"U2","yr":1991,"sa":"over 18 million copies","fa":"Marked a reinvention of U2's sound with industrial and electronic influences","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/7/72/Achtung_Baby.png"},{"n":"The Joshua Tree","ar":"U2","yr":1987,"sa":"over 25 million copies","fa":"Propelled U2 to global superstardom, won Album of the Year at the Grammys","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/6b/The_Joshua_Tree.png"},{"n":"1984","ar":"Van Halen","yr":1984,"sa":"over 10 million copies","fa":"Features the synthesizer-driven hit 'Jump'","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/5f/Van_Halen_-_1984.jpg"},{"n":"Hysteria","ar":"Def Leppard","yr":1987,"sa":"over 25 million copies","fa":"Took nearly three years to record, produced seven hit singles","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/40/Def_Leppard_-_Hysteria_%28vinyl_version%29.jpg"},{"n":"Slippery When Wet","ar":"Bon Jovi","yr":1986,"sa":"over 28 million copies","fa":"The album that turned Bon Jovi into a global arena-rock act","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/ab/Bon_jovi_slippery_when_wet.jpg"},{"n":"Metallica (The Black Album)","ar":"Metallica","yr":1991,"sa":"over 30 million copies","fa":"Brought thrash metal into the mainstream, one of the best-selling albums of the SoundScan era","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/2c/Metallica_-_Metallica_cover.jpg"},{"n":"Master of Puppets","ar":"Metallica","yr":1986,"sa":"over 6 million copies","fa":"Widely regarded as one of the greatest heavy metal albums ever recorded","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/b/b2/Metallica_-_Master_of_Puppets_cover.jpg"},{"n":"Ten","ar":"Pearl Jam","yr":1991,"sa":"over 13 million copies","fa":"A defining album of the early 1990s grunge movement","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/6f/Pearl_Jam_Ten_Alt_Cover.jpg"},{"n":"Tragic Kingdom","ar":"No Doubt","yr":1995,"sa":"over 16 million copies","fa":"Blended ska, pop and rock, launched Gwen Stefani to stardom","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/9/9d/No_Doubt_-_Tragic_Kingdom.png"},{"n":"Hybrid Theory","ar":"Linkin Park","yr":2000,"sa":"over 30 million copies","fa":"Best-selling debut album of the 2000s in the United States","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/2a/Linkin_Park_Hybrid_Theory_Album_Cover.jpg"},{"n":"Music Box","ar":"Mariah Carey","yr":1993,"sa":"over 28 million copies","fa":"Features 'Hero' and 'Without You', among Carey's best-known ballads","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/7/75/Music_Box_Mariah_Carey.png"},{"n":"Cracked Rear View","ar":"Hootie & the Blowfish","yr":1994,"sa":"over 21 million copies","fa":"One of the best-selling debut albums in US history","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/2f/Hootie_%26_the_Blowfish_-_Cracked_Rear_View.jpg"},{"n":"No Fences","ar":"Garth Brooks","yr":1990,"sa":"over 20 million copies","fa":"Features 'Friends in Low Places', a defining country anthem of the 1990s","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/5e/Garth_Brooks-No_Fences_%28album_cover%29.jpg"},{"n":"Confessions on a Dance Floor","ar":"Madonna","yr":2005,"sa":"over 10 million copies","fa":"A continuous dance-mixed album that revitalized Madonna's chart success","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/d/df/Madonna_-_Confessions_on_a_Dance_Floor.png"},{"n":"Saturday Night Fever","ar":"Various Artists / Bee Gees","yr":1977,"sa":"over 40 million copies","fa":"Defined the disco era and remained the best-selling soundtrack for over a decade","im":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/0c/TheBeeGeesSaturdayNightFeveralbumcover.jpg"}